# YT-DO Project Rules

## Stack

- **Runtime**: Bun (`bun run dev` / `bun run start`)
- **HTTP**: Hono on port **9988** (configurable via `PORT`)
- **Database**: SQLite via `bun:sqlite` — schema lives in `src/db.ts`
- **Downloads**: Shell out to **yt-dlp** (720p mp4), never reimplement download logic
- **Notifications**: Telegram Bot API via `fetch`

## Project layout

```
src/
  index.ts          # Server entry, mounts routes
  config.ts         # Env loading (fail fast on missing vars)
  db.ts             # SQLite schema + queries
  routes/
    api.ts          # JSON API (download, verify, stream)
    pages.ts        # HTML admin + watch pages
  services/
    ytdlp.ts        # yt-dlp integration
    telegram.ts     # Telegram messages
  utils/
    password.ts     # Per-video passwords + access tokens
data/               # Gitignored — videos + yt-do.db
```

## Conventions

- Use **relative imports** within `src/` (e.g. `../config`, not `@/config`)
- Keep secrets in `.env` only — never commit `.env` or hardcode tokens
- Video files go under `data/videos/`; metadata in SQLite (`videos` table)
- Stream videos with **Range request** support (`206 Partial Content`) — do not serve as attachment downloads on the watch page
- Each video gets a unique **per-video password**; admin page uses **MASTER_PASSWORD** from env
- Public links use `BASE_URL` (subdomain), not raw IP, in Telegram messages
- Prefer minimal diffs; match existing Hono route and HTML inline-template style

## Adding features

- New API routes → `src/routes/api.ts`
- New pages → `src/routes/pages.ts`
- DB changes → update `src/db.ts` schema + migration-safe `CREATE IF NOT EXISTS`
- New env vars → add to `.env.example` and `src/config.ts`, document in README

## Commands

```bash
bun install
bun run dev      # hot reload
bun run start    # production
```

## External dependencies

- `yt-dlp` must be on PATH (`yt-dlp --version`)
- Reverse proxy (Caddy/nginx) should map `BASE_URL` subdomain → `localhost:9988`
